summary:
I am a geologist with a broad background in Earth Sciences. I have published over 50 professional publications, written one book, edited another one, supervised 52 MSc and 24 PhD students and taught numerous classes in Sedimentology, Petroleum Geology, Reservoir Characterization etc. I also lead field trips, for example in the Karoo (South Africa) and many other parts of this world.
I am also a passionate guitar player, mostly fingerpicking style, and I owe three great guitars (Martin, Taylor, Takamine).
